---

<p><a href="https://www.3scale.net/"><img style="padding: 10px;" src="http://api.report/images/kinlane/3scale-logo.png" alt="" width="350" align="right" /></a></p>
<p>It's out with the old and in with the new. 2014 was a great year for APIs with events old and new, technology launches and APIs expandind to more places. Over the weekend, 3scale posted its <a href="http://www.3scale.net/2015/01/2014-api-year-in-review-last-years-api-predictions/">annual review of the API year</a> and also a set of new predictions for 2015. Hello IoT APIs, SDK generations, Identity, Privacy and much more. No doubt it'll be another vintage year! The predictions in order are:</p>

<ol>
<li>Web API Design Will become a Premium Tech Skill.</li>
<li>API Search and Discovery will Heat Up.</li>
<li>Automated Code Gen and SDKs will Raise the Bar.</li>
<li>Security Breaches will be Top of Mind.</li>
<li>API Operations will Become “A Thing”.</li>
<li>Industry Standards or Shared Specifications will Start Getting Early Traction.</li>
<li>The API Event Scene will Grow.</li>
<li>Realtime and Post Rest APIs.</li>
<li>IoT will Stretch API Architectures.</li>
<li>Identity, Privacy and Data Access will be Key.</li>
</ol>

<p>Check out the details in the original post: <a href="http://www.3scale.net/2015/01/api-predictions-2015/">API Predictions 2015</a>.</p>
